                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/871: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hare</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-15T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 15, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. Your 102, June 12, 6 p.m. Americans may travel on neutral ships proceeding
                    out of Mediterranean through combat areas but they do so at their own risk and
                    contrary to Department’s advice.</p>
                <p>Blanket authority hereby given you to validate passports for one journey through
                    combat area on neutral ships for Americans choosing so to proceed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
